## GitHub Actions ‚Äî Token Usage

Every workflow must use **`secrets.GH_TOKEN`** (the org-level Personal Access Token). This applies to all `actions/checkout`, `gh` CLI calls, and any step that talks to the GitHub API.

```yaml
# ‚úÖ Correct
- uses: actions/checkout@v4
  with:
    token: ${{ secrets.GH_TOKEN }}

env:
  GH_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GH_TOKEN }}
```

```yaml
# ‚ùå Wrong ‚Äî never use these in workflows
token: ${{ github.token }}
token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
```

PHP scripts read the token with: `getenv('GH_TOKEN') ?: getenv('GITHUB_TOKEN')` ‚Äî `GH_TOKEN` is always preferred; `GITHUB_TOKEN` is accepted only as a local-dev fallback.

